Iterable (Top Interface)
    Root interface for collections.
    Allows iteration using loops.

Example:
        for(String name : list){
            System.out.println(name);
        }

Main method: Iterator<T> iterator()


| Type  | Key Feature                  |
| ----- | ---------------------------- |
| List  | Ordered + duplicates allowed |
| Set   | No duplicates                |
| Queue | FIFO structure               |
| Map   | Key-value pairs              |


